frus:attachment.p:
Whereas explorers and scientists of the
signatory states have explored, investigated and charted extensive
regions in Antarctica;

Whereas vast areas have not yet been seen by
man, and large portions of the coasts are inaccessible by ship at all
times because of ice conditions in contiguous seas;

Whereas under Article 77 of the Charter the
trusteeship system may be applied to territories voluntarily placed
under the system by states responsible for their administration;
